      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Note that this will be more expensive than the strncmp that it replaces. The strncmp would halt as soon as a mismatch is found - presumably in the first character or two in most cases. The conversion to StringPiece means that a full strlen has to be performed. I guess if the keys are short enough this doesn\u0027t matter but it still seems wasteful to do a strlen scan followed immediately by a strcmp scan.\n\nThere’s a related problem with StringPieces that carry std::strings that have (accidentally? on purpose?) embedded NULs. It looks like those will be treated as distinct keys when they come in as parameters, but since they’re stored “raw” in the map, the strings will end at the first NUL when dealt with in the map, and when slurped out of the map. The existing implementation doesn’t have this confusion because it’s very clear that it only works with NUL-terminated strings everywhere.",
      "parentUuid": "4406d5c7_ae620e6d",
